replies.bodyText:
Yeah, imo this functionality is most useful for commands, and it would work but client completions would be tricky without falling back to requesting from the server.
If you aren't doing this in commands, you might as well just have a
@Plugin
public class MyPlugin {
    // [...]
    public static ResourceKey key(final String value) {
        return ResourceKey.of(ProjectData.ID, value);
    }
    // [...]
}
style method in your plugin class -- that's what I use on a few platforms.

